msgctxt "dn17:2.12.32"
msgid "8. Brahmalokūpagama "
msgstr "8. Rebirth in the Brahmā Realm "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.13, pts-vp-pli2.196, sc53
msgctxt "dn17:2.13.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, rājā mahāsudassano na cirasseva kālamakāsi. "
msgstr "Not long after that, King Mahāsudassana passed away. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.13.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā manuññaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuttāvissa bhattasammado hoti; evameva kho, ānanda, rañño mahāsudassanassa māraṇantikā vedanā ahosi. "
msgstr "And the feeling he had close to death was like a householder or their child falling asleep after eating a delectable meal. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn17:2.13.3"
msgid "Kālaṅkato ca, ānanda, rājā mahāsudassano sugatiṃ brahmalokaṃ upapajji. "
msgstr "When he passed away King Mahāsudassana was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm. "

#. VAR: kumārakīḷaṃ → … kīḷitaṃ (bj, mr) | … kīḷikaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn17:2.13.4"
msgid "Rājā, ānanda, mahāsudassano caturāsīti vassasahassāni kumārakīḷaṃ kīḷi. "
msgstr "Ānanda, King Mahāsudassana played children’s games for 84,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.13.5"
msgid "Caturāsīti vassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi. "
msgstr "He ruled as viceroy for 84,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.13.6"
msgid "Caturāsīti vassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresi. "
msgstr "He ruled as king for 84,000 years. "

#. VAR: brahmacariyaṃ cari → brahmacariyaṃ ācari (s1-3, km) | brahma­cari­ya­macari (mr)
#. VAR: gihibhūto → gihībhūto (bj, pts1) | gīhibhūto (km)
msgctxt "dn17:2.13.7"
msgid "Caturāsīti vassasahassāni gihibhūto dhamme pāsāde brahmacariyaṃ cari. "
msgstr "He led the spiritual life as a layman in the Palace of Principle for 84,000 years. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.13.8"
msgid "So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago ahosi. "
msgstr "And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.14, pts-vp-pli2.197, sc54
msgctxt "dn17:2.14.1"
msgid "Siyā kho panānanda, evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, Ānanda, you might think: "

msgctxt "dn17:2.14.2"
msgid "‘añño nūna tena samayena rājā mahāsudassano ahosī’ti, "
msgstr "‘Surely King Mahāsudassana must have been someone else at that time?’ "

msgctxt "dn17:2.14.3"
msgid "na kho panetaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ. Ahaṃ tena samayena rājā mahāsudassano ahosiṃ. "
msgstr "But you should not see it like that. I myself was King Mahāsudassana at that time. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn17:2.14.4"
msgid "Mama tāni caturāsīti nagarasahassāni kusāvatīrājadhānippamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti pāsādasahassāni dhammapāsādappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti kūṭāgārasahassāni mahāviyūhakūṭāgārappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti pallaṅkasahassāni sovaṇṇamayāni rūpiyamayāni dantamayāni sāramayāni gonakatthatāni paṭikatthatāni paṭalikatthatāni kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇāni sauttaracchadāni ubhatolohitakūpadhānāni, mama tāni caturāsīti nāgasahassāni sovaṇṇālaṅkārāni sovaṇṇadhajāni hemajālapaṭicchannāni uposathanāgarājappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti assasahassāni sovaṇṇālaṅkārāni sovaṇṇadhajāni hemajālapaṭicchannāni valāhakaassarājappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti rathasahassāni sīhacammaparivārāni byagghacammaparivārāni dīpicammaparivārāni paṇḍukambalaparivārāni sovaṇṇālaṅkārāni sovaṇṇadhajāni hemajālapaṭicchannāni vejayantarathappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti maṇisahassāni maṇiratanappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti itthisahassāni subhaddādevippamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti gahapatisahassāni gahapatiratanappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti khattiyasahassāni anuyantāni pariṇāyakaratanappamukhāni, mama tāni caturāsīti dhenusahassāni duhasandanāni kaṃsūpadhāraṇāni, mama tāni caturāsīti vatthakoṭisahassāni khomasukhumānaṃ kappāsikasukhumānaṃ koseyyasukhumānaṃ kambalasukhumānaṃ, mama tāni caturāsīti thālipākasahassāni sāyaṃ pātaṃ bhattābhihāro abhihariyittha. "
msgstr "Mine were the 84,000 cities, with the royal capital of Kusāvatī foremost. And mine were all the other possessions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.15, pts-vp-pli2.198, sc55
msgctxt "dn17:2.15.1"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsītinagarasahassānaṃ ekaññeva taṃ nagaraṃ hoti, yaṃ tena samayena ajjhāvasāmi yadidaṃ kusāvatī rājadhānī. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 cities, I only stayed in one, the capital Kusāvatī. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti pāsādasahassānaṃ ekoyeva so pāsādo hoti, yaṃ tena samayena ajjhāvasāmi yadidaṃ dhammo pāsādo. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 mansions, I only dwelt in one, the Palace of Principle. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti kūṭāgārasahassānaṃ ekaññeva taṃ kūṭāgāraṃ hoti, yaṃ tena samayena ajjhāvasāmi yadidaṃ mahāviyūhaṃ kūṭāgāraṃ. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 chambers, I only dwelt in the great foyer. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti pallaṅkasahassānaṃ ekoyeva so pallaṅko hoti, yaṃ tena samayena paribhuñjāmi yadidaṃ sovaṇṇamayo vā rūpiyamayo vā dantamayo vā sāramayo vā. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 couches, I only used one, made of gold or silver or ivory or heartwood. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti nāgasahassānaṃ ekoyeva so nāgo hoti, yaṃ tena samayena abhiruhāmi yadidaṃ uposatho nāgarājā. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 bull elephants, I only rode one, the royal bull elephant named Sabbath. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.6"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti assasahassānaṃ ekoyeva so asso hoti, yaṃ tena samayena abhiruhāmi yadidaṃ valāhako assarājā. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 horses, I only rode one, the royal horse named Thundercloud. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.7"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti rathasahassānaṃ ekoyeva so ratho hoti, yaṃ tena samayena abhiruhāmi yadidaṃ vejayantaratho. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 chariots, I only rode one, the chariot named Triumph. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/is-there-such-a-word-as-velamika/2952
msgctxt "dn17:2.15.8"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti itthisahassānaṃ ekāyeva sā itthī hoti, yā tena samayena paccupaṭṭhāti khattiyānī vā vessinī vā. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 women, I was only served by one, a maiden of the aristocratic or merchant classes. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.9"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti vatthakoṭisahassānaṃ ekaṃyeva taṃ dussayugaṃ hoti, yaṃ tena samayena paridahāmi khomasukhumaṃ vā kappāsikasukhumaṃ vā koseyyasukhumaṃ vā kambalasukhumaṃ vā. "
msgstr "Of those 8,400,000,000 cloths, I only wore one pair, made of fine linen, cotton, silk, or wool. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.15.10"
msgid "Tesaṃ kho panānanda, caturāsīti thālipākasahassānaṃ ekoyeva so thālipāko hoti, yato nāḷikodanaparamaṃ bhuñjāmi tadupiyañca sūpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Of those 84,000 servings of food, I only had one, eating at most a serving of rice and suitable sauce. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.16, sc56
msgctxt "dn17:2.16.1"
msgid "Passānanda, sabbete saṅkhārā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā. "
msgstr "See, Ānanda! All those conditioned phenomena have passed, ceased, and perished. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.16.2"
msgid "Evaṃ aniccā kho, ānanda, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "So impermanent are conditions, "

msgctxt "dn17:2.16.3"
msgid "evaṃ addhuvā kho, ānanda, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "so unstable are conditions, "

msgctxt "dn17:2.16.4"
msgid "evaṃ anassāsikā kho, ānanda, saṅkhārā. "
msgstr "so unreliable are conditions. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.16.5"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, ānanda, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccituṃ. "
msgstr "This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.17, pts-vp-pli2.199, sc57
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.1"
msgid "Chakkhattuṃ kho panāhaṃ, ānanda, abhijānāmi imasmiṃ padese sarīraṃ nikkhipitaṃ, tañca kho rājāva samāno cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato, ayaṃ sattamo sarīranikkhepo. "
msgstr "Six times, Ānanda, I recall having laid down my body at this place. And the seventh time was as a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king, at which time my dominion extended to all four sides, I achieved stability in the country, and I possessed the seven treasures. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.17.2"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ, ānanda, taṃ padesaṃ samanupassāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya yattha tathāgato aṭṭhamaṃ sarīraṃ nikkhipeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "But Ānanda, I do not see any place in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans where the Realized One would lay down his body for the eighth time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc58
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "dn17:2.17.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc59
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.5"
msgid "“Aniccā vata saṅkhārā, "
msgstr "“Oh! Conditions are impermanent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.6"
msgid "uppādavayadhammino; "
msgstr "their nature is to rise and fall; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.7"
msgid "Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti, "
msgstr "having arisen, they cease; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.8"
msgid "tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho”ti. "
msgstr "their stilling is true bliss.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn17:2.17.9"
msgid "Mahāsudassanasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

